problems.description:
Write a stored procedure to batch-process salary raises by department.

```sql
DELIMITER //
CREATE PROCEDURE raise_salaries(IN dept_id INT, IN pct DECIMAL(5,2))
BEGIN
  DECLARE done INT DEFAULT FALSE;
  DECLARE emp_id INT;
  DECLARE cur CURSOR FOR SELECT id FROM employees WHERE department_id = dept_id;
  DECLARE CONTINUE HANDLER FOR NOT FOUND SET done = TRUE;
  OPEN cur;
  read_loop: LOOP
    FETCH cur INTO emp_id;
    IF done THEN LEAVE read_loop; END IF;
    UPDATE employees SET salary = salary * (1 + pct/100) WHERE id = emp_id;
  END LOOP;
  CLOSE cur;
END//
```

**Call:** `CALL raise_salaries(1, 10);` — gives 10% raise to dept 1.

